headline: US Cancels Major Solar Project in Nevada Biden Had Supported
summary: The Esmeralda Seven solar farm is now listed as “canceled,” according to the Bureau of Land Management’s website, which was last updated Thursday.  The project, as proposed by developers including NextEra Energy Inc. and Invenergy, comprised seven solar farms spanning 118,000 acres of federal land northwest of Las Vegas.
